  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Presence of an intraoperative hemodynamic instability</measure>
    <time_frame>At the time of surgery (less than 4 hours)</time_frame>
    <description>An intraoperative hemodynamic instability is defined as the occurrence of at least one intraoperative episode of systolic blood pressure ≥ 160 mmHg and at least one episode of mean blood pressure ≤ 60 mmHg</description>
